00:27:06.039 --> 00:27:12.490
in fish oil or marine oils, DHA and EPA those
are required in the brain.

00:27:12.490 --> 00:27:20.649
ALA, the third Omega fat which is a great
anti-inflammatory found in much of the plant

00:27:20.649 --> 00:27:26.480
kingdom is not a substitute no matter what
you've been told.

00:27:26.480 --> 00:27:34.380
On the best day with the best genetic possibilities
when you've eaten the best diet, a maximum

00:27:34.380 --> 00:27:43.400
of five to maybe ten percent of that ALA will
be converted to DHA or EPA.

00:27:43.400 --> 00:27:47.990
So the body just does not have the capacity
to replace it.

00:27:47.990 --> 00:27:57.010
DHA is absolutely essential to the function
of a brain cell; it is what keeps the inflammatory

00:27:57.010 --> 00:28:03.840
processes in the brain cell in check.

00:28:03.840 --> 00:28:11.140
Inflammation and oxidation are a side effect
of being alive; we all have it going on.

00:28:11.140 --> 00:28:17.570
In the brain and in the body we have systems
to help fight this all the time.

00:28:17.570 --> 00:28:24.730
The system that is critical in the brain depends
on the Omega-3 fat DHA.

00:28:24.730 --> 00:28:26.860
[pause]

00:28:26.860 --> 00:28:32.740
Because fat is so essential to the mass of
the brain, 60 percent of the mass of the brain

00:28:32.740 --> 00:28:38.760
is fat, so you must have fat in your diet.

00:28:38.760 --> 00:28:48.149
Because the composition of a brain cell membrane
so depends on DHA and on fat, if DHA isn't

00:28:48.149 --> 00:28:54.350
around it will replace DHA with another fat;
that fat can function structurally but it

00:28:54.350 --> 00:29:03.880
is not a functional anti-inflammatory compound
so that inflammation proceeds unchecked.

00:29:03.880 --> 00:29:12.159
When we have low levels of DHA in the body
brain cells become, neuroscientists call it

00:29:12.159 --> 00:29:15.780
rigid or not plastic.

00:29:15.780 --> 00:29:24.150
We wanna have fluidity in our cells and when
inflammation proceeds in the brain we lose

00:29:24.150 --> 00:29:29.250
that fluidity of those cells, communication
slows down, neurotransmitters and electrical

00:29:29.250 --> 00:29:37.640
impulses cannot move smoothly, cognitive function
is lower, memory is decreased, mood is lowered.

00:29:37.640 --> 00:29:42.850
People who have low levels of DHA in their
diet, people who are low fish eaters, have

00:29:42.850 --> 00:29:49.169
a significantly increased risk of depression,
not to mention all the other degenerative

00:29:49.169 --> 00:29:56.320
diseases of the brain, and many other certainly
heart disease and other diseases in the body.

00:29:56.320 --> 00:30:00.000
We are finding that these compounds are critically
important.

00:30:00.000 --> 00:30:08.909
If you don't supplement with anything, you
must supplement with DHA and EPA.

00:30:08.909 --> 00:30:16.990
If don't want to supplement and you love fish,
five fish meals a week will get you to the

00:30:16.990 --> 00:30:25.620
amount of recommended fish oil at this point
which is about 1,000 milligrams total every

00:30:25.620 --> 00:30:26.720
day.

00:30:26.720 --> 00:30:28.960
So this is critically important.

