Now I have a great story to tell you with
Matt Hasselbeck's permission.

00:35:30.960 --> 00:35:35.510
I worked with him a number of years ago when
he was getting injured a lot and he needed

00:35:35.510 --> 00:35:38.290
to pack on some pounds.

00:35:38.290 --> 00:35:49.119
And so this is just an illustration of how
if we crave foods, if we don't feed ourselves

00:35:49.119 --> 00:35:57.670
well, our brain will force us to eat certain
things that cravings and desires and what

00:35:57.670 --> 00:36:06.120
feel like uncontrollable urges with food often
can be purely physiological drives that can

00:36:06.120 --> 00:36:12.520
be altered if you change the way you eat.

00:36:12.520 --> 00:36:19.200
Matt was known as the ice cream boy in the
Seahawks training facility.

00:36:19.200 --> 00:36:22.890
When I walked in the first day to work with
him all the guys were snickering.

00:36:22.890 --> 00:36:27.850
And I walked in and I thought, "God is my
fly down, I mean why is everybody laughin'?"

00:36:27.850 --> 00:36:34.150
I get down and I sit down with he and his
lovely wife and I said, "What's gonna on?

00:36:34.150 --> 00:36:36.700
Why was everybody laughing when I walked in?"

00:36:36.700 --> 00:36:41.420
"Oh," he said, "they've all taken bets on
me workin' with you and who's gonna win the

00:36:41.420 --> 00:36:42.820
dietician or me."

00:36:42.820 --> 00:36:43.860
I said, "Why?"

00:36:43.860 --> 00:36:47.010
"Well," he says, "let me tell you what I eat."

00:36:47.010 --> 00:36:53.320
So he told me what he ate during the day and
then when he got home in the evening he'd

00:36:53.320 --> 00:36:58.000
eat about a quart or more of Haagen-Dazs.

00:36:58.000 --> 00:37:05.680
And when he would get on the plane to go to
an away game, on the plane for the return

00:37:05.680 --> 00:37:10.660
he would have five or six Dove bars.

00:37:10.660 --> 00:37:12.619
[laughter]

00:37:12.619 --> 00:37:20.250
So was this an outta control athlete just
taking advantage of the position that he was

00:37:20.250 --> 00:37:27.710
in and how active he was or was this some
fundamental physiological need for ice cream?

00:37:27.710 --> 00:37:34.760
Well after I talked with Matt he told me that
during the day he ate around 1,500 calories

00:37:34.760 --> 00:37:41.200
worth of food and he trained at least three
times during the day, sometimes four, he'd

00:37:41.200 --> 00:37:49.230
do his morning workout, his strength program
in the training room, they had the team training

00:37:49.230 --> 00:37:54.531
at some point in the morning, he'd have quarterback
skills and drills, they'd train again in the

00:37:54.531 --> 00:38:01.510
afternoon and so by the time he'd get home
he said, "About 1,500 calories."

00:38:01.510 --> 00:38:06.980
Well the guy needed 5,000 calories a day just
to maintain his weight.

00:38:06.980 --> 00:38:10.440
So when he got home he was starving.

00:38:10.440 --> 00:38:12.200
What did the brain say?

00:38:12.200 --> 00:38:14.020
"Immediate fuel.

00:38:14.020 --> 00:38:21.730
I need structural component, I need to raise
my mood, and I need fuel, sugar and fat."

00:38:21.730 --> 00:38:24.450
What better thing than ice cream?

00:38:24.450 --> 00:38:31.510
So I put together a program for Matt that
gave him around 3,000, 3,500 calories during

00:38:31.510 --> 00:38:37.869
the day, much of that in liquid nutrition
using smoothies and if you ever see my book

00:38:37.869 --> 00:38:43.980
Power Eating it is packed with recovery drinks
and smoothies; it is a very important part

00:38:43.980 --> 00:38:50.180
of an active person's life whether or not
you're burnin' 5,000 calories a day or 1,600

00:38:50.180 --> 00:38:55.820
calories a day we are runnin' around a lot
and liquid smoothie packed nutrition is a

00:38:55.820 --> 00:38:57.530
great convenience.

00:38:57.530 --> 00:39:03.280
So for Matt he had between food and smoothies
around 3,500 calories a day.

00:39:03.280 --> 00:39:08.550
When he got home he had a really nice dinner
and of course I still had about I don't know

00:39:08.550 --> 00:39:13.010
cup and a half of ice cream in his diet.

00:39:13.010 --> 00:39:15.960
And people say to me, "You kept ice cream
in it?"

00:39:15.960 --> 00:39:20.910
Well yeah I mean he could eat 5,000 calories
a day and if I gave the guy who was eatin'

00:39:20.910 --> 00:39:25.900
that much ice cream a diet with no ice cream
he'd say, "Hey, doc you're a nice lady but

00:39:25.900 --> 00:39:27.380
I'm not gonna follow this diet."

00:39:27.380 --> 00:39:28.380
Right?

00:39:28.380 --> 00:39:32.490
[chuckles] So we kept the ice cream in there
in the evening.

00:39:32.490 --> 00:39:40.430
After about a week, 10 days, Matt called and
he said, "Hey doc, is there a healthier snack

00:39:40.430 --> 00:39:41.560
I could eat at night.

00:39:41.560 --> 00:39:45.869
I don't even want that ice cream anymore."

00:39:45.869 --> 00:39:54.119
So with all the permission in the world his
body was well fed, his brain was well fed,

00:39:54.119 --> 00:39:56.160
he didn't want that anymore.

